    "id": "e9KqX3a",
    "title": "Parent Teacher Conferences",
    "author": "Sarah Macintosh",
    "show_author": true,
    "editable": false,
    "lead": "<strong>Parent Teacher Conferences are being held on Tuesday 27th May and Thursday 29th May</strong>",
    "body": "<p>In Week 5 we will be holding Parent Teacher Conferences.</p>\n\n<p>We will be discussing the report that will be going home in Week 4, as well as how your child has settled into the year, their progress and things you can help with at home.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Online Bookings:</strong><br></p>\n\n<p>MNS use an online booking system to organise appointment times for parent teacher conferences. Please follow this link: <a href=\"http://www.schoolinterviews.co.nz/code/yhxvc\">School Interviews</a> and enter the event code <strong>hc5fa</strong><br></p>\n\n<p>Children are welcome to join the meeting if you would like them to.<br></p>\n\n<p>Here’s how it works:</p>\n\n<ul><li><p>Parents choose the teachers and times <em>they</em> want, removing any chance of timetable conflicts. You will be able to book everything in a couple of minutes, instead of waiting for notification back from school a few days later.&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Parents get an emailed confirmation of their interviews, and can confirm, cancel or reschedule on the internet at any time.</p></li><li><p>Parent and child information is as safe as can be, without imposing draconian security measures. The school office use a secure login system to access administration functions, designed according to internet best practices.<br></p><p>Families without internet access can still make appointment times.&nbsp; Belinda in the school office will handle counter or phone bookings on behalf of parents without access to a computer, call on 04 388 6657 for assistance.</p></li></ul>\n\n<p><br></p>",
