    "editable": false,
    "lead": null,
    "body": "<p>MNS students worked incredibly hard in Term 1 to earn TIKA tickets by showing our TIKA values - Teamwork, Integrity, Kindness and Ako.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>The TIKA jars were full and as a result, we held a TIKA celebration day on Friday 11th April.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>The theme for this day was: EXPLORING / EXPLORATION / EXPLORERS. This is our school inquiry focus this year as we explore more about ourselves, our culture, our environment, the arts etc.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Last year, our Pōhutukawa student leaders collected ideas from students across the school about HOW they would like to celebrate.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Students dressed up as EXPLORERS or in the TIKA colours.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>We had a school-wide discovery time with a focus on exploration and ate our lunch together as a school.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>We look forward to filling those TIKA jars with TIKA tickets in Term 2 as well. The class with the most TIKA tickets this term, get a special class treat at the end of the term!</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Each week, we have a whole school TIKA Ticket prize draw and one lucky student gets a special Principal's Award from Mrs Adam in recognition of them showing the TIKA values.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>For more information about PB4L at Miramar North School, visit: <a href=\"https://www.mns.school.nz/positive-behaviour-for-learning/\">https://www.mns.school.nz/positive-behaviour-for-learning/</a></p>",
